    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.34,
      "end": 7.42,
      "text": "This is a Librabox recording. All Librabox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.42,
      "end": 12.78,
      "text": "information and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit Librabox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.62,
      "end": 22.82,
      "text": "Recording by Gitu Milwani. Aseb's Fables, The Wild Ball and The Fox. A wild ball was engaged",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 22.82,
      "end": 28.96,
      "text": "in hetting his tests upon the trunk of a tree in the forest when the fox came by and seeing",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 28.96,
      "end": 33.72,
      "text": "what he was there to sit to him. Why are you doing that, Pray? The huntsmen are not out",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 33.72,
      "end": 39.62,
      "text": "today and there are no other dangers at hand that I can see. True, my friend, replied the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 39.62,
      "end": 44.94,
      "text": "war, but the instant my life is in danger, I shall need to use my tasks. There will be",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 44.94,
      "end": 50.54,
      "text": "no time to sharpen them then. End of The Wild Ball and The Fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
